## Preview options

Choose the path that matches your setup:

### Option 1 — Browser (fastest, no install)

```bash
cd mobile
npm install
cp .env.example .env          # set EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL
npx expo start --web
```

Opens at `http://localhost:8081` in your browser. NativeWind v4 renders correctly on web.
No Android Studio, no Xcode, no Expo account needed.

---

### Option 2 — Physical device via EAS development build (recommended for mobile)

```bash
npm install -g eas-cli
eas login
eas build --platform android --profile development   # or ios
```

EAS builds a `.apk` / `.ipa` (free tier: ~15 min). Install it on your device, then:

```bash
npx expo start
```

Scan the QR code with the **EAS dev build** app (not Expo Go). Full NativeWind v4 styling.

> **Why not Expo Go?** Expo Go doesn't run your project's Babel plugins, so NativeWind
> `className` props are silently ignored and the UI renders unstyled.

---

### Option 3 — Local simulator / emulator

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env
npx expo run:ios        # requires macOS + Xcode 15+
npx expo run:android    # requires Android Studio + emulator
```

Builds locally — no EAS account needed. Full NativeWind v4 support.

---

### Option 4 — Shareable preview APK (share with team / stakeholders)

```bash
eas build --platform android --profile preview
```

Produces a QR-code download link. Anyone with an Android device can install it directly
(no Play Store, no developer mode on iOS). Build takes ~15 min on EAS free tier.

