## Crash reporting (Sentry)

1. Create a project at [sentry.io](https://sentry.io) for React Native
2. Set `EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN` in `.env` and in `eas.json` env blocks
3. Install the Sentry SDK: `npx expo install @sentry/react-native`
4. Run the wizard to patch `babel.config.js`: `npx @sentry/wizard@latest -i reactNative`

`initSentry()` is called at app startup in `app/_layout.tsx` and is a no-op when `EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN` is not set, so development builds work without configuration.

